      <p>Winter nights in Orange, CA might not be brutal by national standards — but when your furnace stops working and the temperature drops to the low 40s, it feels plenty cold inside. That's exactly when you need someone you can call without worrying about getting oversold or overcharged.</p>
      <p>At HiLo Heating & Air Conditioning, we've been helping homeowners across Orange County stay warm since 2000. We do <strong>furnace repair Orange</strong> residents can count on — straightforward diagnostics, honest pricing, and repairs that actually hold up. No unnecessary upsells, no inflated quotes. Just a technician who shows up, figures out what's wrong, and fixes it.</p>

      <h2>How Do You Know It's Time to Call for Furnace Repair?</h2>
      <p>Furnaces tend to give you hints before they completely give out. The trick is catching those hints before a manageable issue turns into a full system failure on the coldest night of the year.</p>
      <p>Keep an eye out for these warning signs:</p>
      <ul>
        <li>Your home takes much longer than usual to reach the temperature you've set</li>
        <li>The furnace kicks on and off in short bursts without properly heating the space</li>
        <li>You're hearing banging, rattling, or squealing sounds that weren't there before</li>
        <li>Some rooms feel warm while others stay cold no matter what</li>
        <li>There's a burning smell when the heat first turns on — or it lingers</li>
        <li>Your gas or electric bill has crept up without any change in usage habits</li>
        <li>The pilot light keeps going out, or it's burning yellow instead of blue</li>
      </ul>
      <p>Any of these things can point to something specific — a faulty igniter, a dirty flame sensor, a blower motor issue, a cracked heat exchanger, or airflow problems caused by a clogged filter. Our technicians diagnose the actual cause rather than guessing or replacing parts unnecessarily.</p>

      <h2>What We Fix</h2>
      <p>For <strong>furnace repair Orange</strong> homeowners call us about, we handle the full range of issues: ignition system failures, gas valve problems, heat exchanger inspections, thermostat calibration, blower motor repairs, control board issues, and duct-related airflow problems. We work on all major brands — Carrier, Trane, Lennox, Goodman, Rheem, York, and more — and our trucks are stocked with common parts so most repairs wrap up in a single visit.</p>

      <h2>Why Orange Homeowners Choose HiLo</h2>
      <p>Plenty of HVAC companies serve Orange. What makes people call us back — and refer their neighbors — comes down to a few consistent things.</p>
      <p>We're local, we've been here since 2000, and we treat every home like it's our own. When you call us for <strong>furnace repair Orange</strong> service, you're not going through a call center or waiting days for a callback. You get a real team that responds quickly, communicates clearly, and doesn't pad the bill.</p>
      <p>We also don't push replacements when a repair makes more sense. If your furnace can be fixed reliably, that's what we'll recommend. If it genuinely can't — because of age, a cracked heat exchanger, or the cost math just doesn't work — we'll tell you that too and walk you through your options honestly.</p>
      <p>Every repair we do is backed by a warranty. If something isn't right after we've been out, we come back and make it right.</p>
